title: Bug 109350: Output parameter not displayed in data set dialog
OB: Output parameter not displayed in data set dialog.
EB: Output parameter should be displayed in the data set dialog. Details of the output parameter should also be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR: To reproduce the issue: 1. Execute a stored procedure from the Oracle database. 2. Check if the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. 3. Open the query result page. 4. Verify that no data is returned but the output parameter should be displayed in the data set dialog.
